<Docs title="Claude Subscription Path" description="Fastest path to a working Omegon session using Claude Pro/Max.">
  <h1>Claude Subscription Path</h1>
  <p>
    This is the shortest happy path for many operators. If you have Claude Pro or Max,
    use browser login and get to a first successful prompt before touching advanced settings.
  </p>

  <h2>What you need</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Omegon installed</li>
    <li>A git repo or project directory</li>
    <li>Claude Pro or Max access</li>
    <li>A browser available on the same machine</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Steps</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><code>{snippet("auth.login_anthropic")}</code></li>
    <li>Complete browser authentication</li>
    <li><code>cd</code> into a project and run <code>{snippet("quickstart.start_full")}</code></li>
    <li>Send this prompt: <code>Read README.md and summarize this project in 5 bullets.</code></li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Success signal</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>You see a normal assistant response, not an auth/provider error</li>
    <li>You see at least one tool card such as <code>read</code></li>
    <li>The response references your actual repo contents</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>If it fails</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>If browser login succeeds but Omegon still errors, run <code>{snippet("slash.auth_status_slash")}</code></li>
    <li>If the wrong provider appears active, run <code>{snippet("slash.model")}</code> and select the Claude-backed route</li>
    <li>If this guide is wrong or incomplete, file a <strong>Setup problem</strong> issue and say you followed the Claude subscription path</li>
  </ul>
</Docs>
